stylometry: Bayes Theorom is a method used for applying additional information to change probabilities. Bayes theorem is important because it allows you to look at the posterior probability, given states of nature. To determine the posterior probability, you look at the prior probabilities and the conditional probabilities, given states of nature.We need posterior probabilities because it allows us to see the end result of the problem. An example is drug testing athletes at a college. Using information already known for the prior probability, Baye's Theorem can determine the posterior probabilitiy of the number of athletes that either failed or passed the drug test.
